 :tx/rationale "Create task: ACP-4: Implement compute_action_from_store() — unified R(t) action extraction (INV-BUDGET-009, INV-GUIDANCE-010). BACKGROUND: The guidance system R(t) already computes the highest-impact task recommendation. ACP unifies this with the output system: compute_action_from_store(store) -> ProjectedAction extracts the R(t) top recommendation and returns it as a ProjectedAction. This is the SINGLE CODE PATH for action computation — both the guidance footer and the projection action come from here. Currently, the footer calls compute_routing_from_store() and the status command calls it separately. ACP makes them the same call. The function: (1) calls compute_routing_from_store(), (2) takes the top-impact task, (3) formats it as ProjectedAction { command: 'braid go <id>', rationale: '<title excerpt>', impact }. When no tasks exist, returns a default action (braid observe, braid harvest, etc.) based on store state. APPROACH: Add compute_action_from_store(store: &Store) -> ProjectedAction to guidance.rs. Reuse existing compute_routing_from_store(). Handle edge cases: empty store -> 'braid init', no tasks -> 'braid observe', harvest overdue -> 'braid harvest --commit'. Tests: (A) store with tasks returns top R(t) as action. (B) empty store returns 'braid observe'. (C) store with overdue harvest returns 'braid harvest'. (D) action.command is always a valid braid CLI command. FILE: crates/braid-kernel/src/guidance.rs"
